Detailed Description

template<class Key, class T, class HashFunction = hash<Key>, class KeyEqual = std::equal_to<Key>, class DiscardFunction = DiscardIgnore< pair<Key,T> >, class Allocator = std::allocator< pair<Key,T> >>
class mm::cache_map< Key, T, HashFunction, KeyEqual, DiscardFunction, Allocator >

Cache map.

Implements a map container like std::hash_map, but with a fixed element number.

Template Parameters

  • Key : The key type of the map.

  • T : The hash_map's data type. This is also defined as hash_map::data_type.

  • HashFunction : Callable hasher.

  • DiscardFunction : Discarded item manager.

Definition at line 312 of file cache_map.hpp.

template<class Key, class T, class HashFunction = hash<Key>, class KeyEqual = std::equal_to<Key>, class DiscardFunction = DiscardIgnore< pair<Key,T> >, class Allocator = std::allocator< pair<Key,T> >>
pair<iterator,bool> mm::cache_map< Key, T, HashFunction, KeyEqual, DiscardFunction, Allocator >::insert ( const value_type &  obj  )  [inline]

Insert an item in the map.

The item, the pair(key, data), will be inserted in the hash table. In case of a key hash collision, the inserted item will replace the existing one.

Following the DiscardFunction policy there will be a notification that old item has been replaced.

Returns:
A pair<iterator,bool> which contain an iterator to the inserted item and true if the item was correctly inserted, or false if the item was not inserted.
